SIMPLE: humane
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Humane
<hw>Hu*mane"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>humanus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>humain</ets>. See <er>Human</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to man; human.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having the feelings and inclinations creditable to
man; having a disposition to treat other human beings or animals with
kindness; kind; benevolent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of an exceeding courteous and <qex>humane</qex> inclination.</q>
<rj><qau>Sportswood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Humanizing; exalting; tending to refine.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Kind; sympathizing; benevolent; mild;
compassionate; gentle; tender; merciful.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Hu*mane"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Hu*mane"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 712 --></p>

<p><ent>Humanics</ent>⟦br⟧
